participant_id.Description: Unique BIDS identifier for the participant in this study.

subjectkey.Description: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject

src_subject_id.Description: Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project

interview_date.Description: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

interview_age.Description: Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging. | Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

sex.Description: Sex of subject at birth | M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

eventname.Description: The event name for which the data was collected

wps_q1_y.Description: I get as much information as I can. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_q2_y.Description: I think hard about what steps to take. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_q3_y.Description: I think about the choices before I do anything. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_q4_y.Description: I think of different ways to take care of it. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_q5_y.Description: I try different ways to solve the problem. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_q6_y.Description: I do something to try to solve the problem. | 1 = Never; 2 = A Little; 3 = Sometimes; 4 = Pretty Often; 5 = Usually

wps_admin.Description: Please indicate how instrument was administered: | 1=RA-Administered ; 2=Youth Self-Administered ; 3=Combination [event_name_number] > '21'
